716335f-a.text:
The house in the rear of No. 1915 Amsterdam Ave., adjoining the S.E. corner of 155th Street.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 496.

716334f-a.text:
Amsterdam Ave., south from West 155th Street. On the right appears the eastern edge of Trinity Cemetery, across which appears the spire of the Washington Heights M.E. Church. The cemetery couples the west side of the Ave. from 155th to 153rd Streets, while the Church is at the S.W. corner of the letter.
August 27, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.

716333f-a.text:
Amsterdam Avenue, north across West 155th Street. Prominently shown is the west side of this thoroughfare. A portion of Trinity Cemetery appears at the left. This is to the south of 155th Street. View No. 2. is limited to the 155th-156th Street frontage. Note the Whalen Furniture Co. at the S. W. corner of 156th Street.

May 19, 1940
No's. 1-2

P. L. Sperr
